stream
BT /F2 21 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 744 Tm (AspieDad Communication Guide) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 726 Tm (A one-page summary with practical communication help for both NT and Aspie readers.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 694 Tm (Research-based framing for spoken communication) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 678 Tm (Research on spoken communication suggests that the clearest exchanges are brief,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 664 Tm (concrete, and focused on one main point at a time, rather than combining) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 650 Tm (multiple layers of emotion and explanation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 636 Tm (A useful starting point is to allow about 10 seconds of space before continuing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 622 Tm (Of course, this may vary depending on the listener, stress levels,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 608 Tm (environmental factors, and how well you know each other.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 576 Tm (3 Helpful Tactics For NT Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 558 Tm (1. Be direct and specific.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 544 Tm (Say the real need clearly instead of hinting or expecting it to be inferred.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 526 Tm (2. Use one issue at a time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 512 Tm (Break information into short, manageable chunks and check understanding before adding more.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 494 Tm (3. Slow down and pause.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 480 Tm (Do not fill silence with more language too quickly. Processing time is often part of understanding.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 448 Tm (3 Helpful Tactics For Aspie Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 430 Tm (1. Say the care out loud.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 416 Tm (Do not assume your love or concern is obvious. NT spouses often need it spoken clearly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 398 Tm (2. Acknowledge feelings before facts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 384 Tm (Start with: "I can see this hurt you" before moving into logic, analysis, or correction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 366 Tm (3. Return after processing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 352 Tm (If you need time, say so directly and come back. Silence without return can feel like rejection.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 320 Tm (3 Simple Phrases For NT Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 304 Tm (1. "I am going to keep this short and clear.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 290 Tm (2. "Can you tell me what you heard me say?") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 276 Tm (3. "We can stay with one issue at a time.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 248 Tm (3 Simple Phrases For Aspie Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 232 Tm (1. "I care about you, even if I am struggling to show it.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 218 Tm (2. "I need a few minutes to process, but I will come back.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 204 Tm (3. "Do you want comfort, help, or for me just to listen?") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 88 Tm (AspieDad.com | Building understanding between NT and Aspie family life) Tj ET
